This is how it works:


Check version number sanity:

  java -jar target/pomutils-1.0.0-app.jar <pomfile> -s

This will cross check all version numbers in the source tree, and
print out inconsistencies.



Print all versions:

  java -jar target/pomutils-1.0.0-app.jar <pomfile> -p



Change the version of an artifact, and fix its direct dependencies:

  java -jar target/pomutils-1.0.0-app.jar <pomfile> -vgroupId:artifact:version

Sets the versoin number of groupId:artifact to version in all the poms
it is referred.


Change the versions of artifacts:

  java -jar target/pomutils-1.0.0-app.jar <pomfile> -ffile

Sets the version numbers of all artifacts in <file>


So, print all versions, redirect the output to a text file. Then,
edito the file to set the new version numbers, and feed it back using
the -f switch.

